The Hecke field `K = ℚ(α)` is degree 12 over ℚ. The LMFDB lists q-coefficients as
elements of `K`, which we decompose as `c_0 + c_1 · α + … + c_{11} · α^11`.
The combined form is `f = f_0 + α · f_1 + … + α^11 · f_{11}`, with each
`f_j` a level-1 weight-152 form with rational coefficients in `(E₄, E₆)`.

